<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seized Narcotic Drugs Destroyed in Vientiane </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seized Narcotic Drugs Destroyed in Vientiane </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2506131494 Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network in 
Lao 1200 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2506131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane Vitthayou Hengsat Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lao </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] On the occasion of the world antinarcotics day 
on 26 June, on the morning of 25 June the people's court of 
Vientiane Municipality held a ceremony to destroy seized 
narcotic drugs at the Justice Ministry in the presence of Souban 
Salitthilat, deputy foreign affairs minister and chairman of the 
National Committee for the Suppression and Control of Narcotic 
Drugs. 
  Attending the ceremony were diplomats and foreign 
dignitaries 
as well as a number of Lao authorities concerned. The destroyed 
drugs, worth more than 45 million kips, included 10 kilos of 
heroin, 120 kilos of opium, more than 170 kilos of marijuana, 
and 14,000 packages of "Buat Hai" pain killers. These drugs 
were seized by Lao authorities along border areas and in post 
offices throughout the country. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

