<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   MP's Urge Restraint Over Press Ban Protests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MP's Urge Restraint Over Press Ban Protests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806153994 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2806153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The parliamentary Functional Group has asked all 
sides, particularly security forces and demonstrrators, to 
exercise self-restraint. Several members of the group made the 
appeal during a news conference in Jakarta today. On the 
occasion, Abdullah Alatas Fahmi, chairman of the Department of 
Information, Publication, and Mass Media of the Functional Group 
Central Executive Council, asked the security forces to handle 
demonstrations proportionally and not execessively. On the 
other hand, the demonstrators were asked to exercise 
self-restraint in order not to complicate the situation. 
  Meanwhile, Abu Hassan Sazili, vice chairman of the 
parliamentary Functional Group, stressed the need for all sides 
to coolly respond to the situation in the wake of the license 
revocation of several publications. 
  Sugeng Wijaya, member of parliamentary Commission I [Roman 
numeral one, in charge of foreign affairs, defense, security, 
and information] reminded the press circles not to be afraid of 
carrying out their duties and roles if they are carried out in 
accordance with the journalistic ethics. 

</TEXT>

