<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Journalists Association Urges `Self-Restraint' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Journalists Association Urges `Self-Restraint' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806145294 Jakarta ANTARA in English 1317 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2806145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta ANTARA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, June 28 (ANEX-ANTARA) -- The Central 
Executive Board of the Indonesian Journalists Association (PWI) 
told its members here Tuesday to maintain self-restraint so they 
would not be carried away by activities outside the PWI 
regulations. 
  In a statement signed by Chairman Tribuana Said and 
Secretary 
General Parni Hadi, PWI expressed its worries that 
demonstrations as a follow up of the recent closure of three 
Jakarta weeklies might only ruin efforts still being worked out 
by the association to solve the banning problem. 
  PWI noted that demonstrations have been used as a means of 
expression of various aspirations which might further complicate 
things. 
  Therefore, the association called on all of its members to 
always uphold previous statements which among others expressed 
concerns over the banning. 
  However, at the same time, the statements expressed 
understanding as well over the government's reasons behind such 
a decision. 
  PWI, the Tuesday's statement said, had encouraged the 
government to issue a new press publication permit so that all 
PWI members previously affiliated to the three banned weeklies 
would not be left without employment for too long. 
  It further said that as long as legal and professional 
mechanism are upheld by all the concerned parties, revocation of 
press publication permit would not take place again in the 
future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-30653 </DOCNO>
