<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Established To Deal With AIDS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Established To Deal With AIDS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2906095794 Jakarta ANTARA in English 1633 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2906095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta ANTARA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, June 28 (OANA-ANTARA) -- The government has 
set up an inter-ministerial commission to deal with Acquired 
Immunity Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), the deadly disease which is 
also on the rise in Indonesia, it was announced here Tuesday. 
  Secretary of the Office of the Coordinating Minister of 
People's Welfare Suyono Yahya said the commission -- created by 
a presidential decree, bore the task of fighting the spread and 
"not the victims" of the incurable disease. 
  The commission would launch programmes to fight AIDS not 
only 
at national and provincial levels but at district level as well, 
Yahya said. 
  He said the commission's programmes would emphasize efforts 
at preventing people from contracting HIV, the virus that leads 
to AIDS. 
  The commission would also disseminate information on AIDS 
designed to let the public have the right knowledge and 
understanding of the disease. This was necessary to prevent the 
public from unduly becoming restive when encountering or having 
to live with actual AIDS cases. 
  Coordinating Minister for People's Welfare Azwar Anas is 
chairman of the commission while four other cabinet ministers, 
namely Health Minister Suyudi, Religious Affairs Minister 
Tarmizi Taher, Social Affairs Minister Inten Suweno and State 
Minister for Population Affairs Haryono Suyono will be members. 
  The following cabinet ministers are also involved in the 
commission: Information Minister Harmoko, Tourism, Post and 
Telecommunications Minister Joop Ave, Home Affairs Minister Yogi 
S. Memed and Youth and Sports Minister Hayono Isman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

