<H3> <TI>   New Vessel Launched for Spratlys Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Vessel Launched for Spratlys Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806074294 Hanoi VNA in English 0647 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2806074294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 28 -- A sea vessel named Truong Sa-10 
has been launched recently by the Ha Long shipyard. 
  The 70.75-metre-long and 11.8-metre-wide ship has a design 
capacity of 1,000 tonnes and is provided with modern equipment. 
  This transport ship was specially built in service of the 
Truong Sa archipelago [Spratlys]. 
  In the first half of this year, the Truong Sa Marine Product 
Company maintained the operation of all its ships. The company 
has well combined its tasks of economic production, scientific 
surveys and national defence. It discovered and prevented 
dozens of foreign vessels from illegally operating in the 
country's territorial waters and continental shelf. 

</TEXT>

