<H3> <TI>   Lao Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavat Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lao Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavat Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Received by Party Leader </H4>

<F P=102> BK2806142594 Hanoi VNA in English 1402 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2806142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 28 -- Party General Secretary Do 
Muoi received here this afternoon Lao Foreign Minister Somsavat 
Lengsavat who is on a visit to Vietnam. 
  The Lao chief diplomat conveyed regards from president of 
the 
Lao People's Revolutionary Party Central Committee Khamtai 
Siphandon to Mr. Do Muoi. 
  He also expressed his satisfaction at the development of the 
special friendship, fraternal solidarity and all-sided 
cooperation between the two parties, states and peoples. He 
affirmed that Laos always respected and strived for the constant 
consolidation and further promotion of those traditional 
relations. 
  Speaking to his guest, General Secretary Do Muoi welcomed 
the 
Lao foreign minister's visit and the results of the talks 
between the two foreign ministers. He said that the two sides 
should exchange views and experiences with each other, 
strengthen the effective and all-sides cooperation and promote 
the special solidarity between the two countries. 

