<H3> <TI>   Lang Son Supplies More Electricity to Districts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lang Son Supplies More Electricity to Districts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2706091794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2706091794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Lang Son provincial electric power service 
recently started the construction of three 35-kilovolt power 
lines: the first one spans from Quoc Khanh town to Trang Dinh 
district, the second from Cao Loc town to the border district of 
Ba Son, and the third for new economic zones in the province. 
  Lang Son has, thus far, supplied electricity to 11 districts 
and towns through the national grid. The three new power lines 
is aimed at supplying electricity for the development of rural 
area and zones inhabited by ethnic minorities. 

