<F P=106> [Weekly news conference by President Fidel V. Ramos with </F>
domestic and foreign correspondents at Malacanang Palace in 
Manila -- live] 
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] On the Korean summit, you're 
familiar with the developments? The two heads of state 
concerned, the president of the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea and the Republic of Korea -- President Kim Il-song and 
President Kim Yong-sam, respectively -- have agreed to meet in 
Pyongyang late July after some preliminary conferences by 
subordinate officials. And I would like to see this as opening 
up a new era of regional stability in the Asia-Pacific region. 
I therefore convey our admiration for the two Korean leaders 
for showing statesmanship in pursuing the path of peace rather 
than the path of belligerent confrontation. You will recall that 
this has been our consistent policy at the height of the nuclear 
confrontation in the Korean peninsula, and even before. 
  Questions so far? 
  I also would like to inform everyone that I am satisfied 
with 
the conclusion of the first round of negotiations between the 
Philippines and Indonesia on the delimiting, or the 
identification, of our maritime boundary. And I would like to 
point out that this opens up some opportunities for us to have, 
perhaps, a fishing agreement and thereby eliminate previous 
difficulties and confrontations which have taken place in the 
absence of such agreements. [passage omitted] 

