<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: Warning to Australian Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman: Warning to Australian Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2906124994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2906124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry spokesman has been authorized 
to respond to the statement made on BBC radio on 27 June by a 
member of the Australian Parliament consultative delegation that 
will soon visit Vietnam, in which it was said that the main 
purpose of the visit would be to examine the human rights issue. 
  Vietnam agreed to receive the Australian Parliament 
consultative delegation in the name of developing bilateral 
relations between the two countries on the basis of equality, 
respect for each other's sovereignty, and mutually beneficial 
cooperation. The purpose of the visit is to exchange views on 
issues of mutual concern, particularly measures to promote 
cooperation. Following several meetings, both sides clearly 
understood this. Any activities that are not in line with this 
agreement or that intervene in Vietnam's internal affairs would 
be inappropriate. They could undermine the visit and harm the 
cooperative relations between the two countries, which have been 
developing favorably. 

</TEXT>

