<F P=102>   LD2905182094 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
1730 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2905182094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gyula Horn, leader of the Hungarian Socialist Party, 
who is the most likely candidate for the post of future 
Hungarian prime minister, said that the next Budapest government 
will advocate cultural autonomy for national minorities in 
neighboring states. In cases where a Hungarian minority is in 
effect a majority, the Hungarian Socialist chairman proposes 
administrative autonomy. This does not mean, however, we will be 
seeking to entice Hungarian minorities in neighboring states to 
strive for territorial autonomy or even separation, Horn added. 

</TEXT>

