<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders React to MSZP Election Victory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Party Leaders React to MSZP Election Victory </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    KDNP Chairman on `Pro-National' Bloc </H4>

<F P=102> LD3005020894 Budapest Duna TV in Hungarian 2345 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3005020894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Duna TV </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Christian Democratic People's Party [KDNP] 
has won 22 parliamentary seats and come in fifth in the 
Hungarian parliamentary elections. KDNP Party Chairman Laszlo 
Surjan assesses the result and the future. 
  [Begin recording] [Surjan] [passage omitted] As we know, the 
transformation from a planned to a market economy and many other 
circumstances have brought very great disappointment because 
only very few people have attained a higher standard of living. 
In practice, the living standard of all citizens has declined. 
  Until now we have had a role in a coalition, a role we 
played 
as a partner of that coalition with moderate strength. Now we 
would like to participate in Hungarian public life in a much 
more marked manner and with a much better defined character but 
independently of others, relying on our own strength and our own 
ideas. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Does it mean that the KDNP 
cannot accept fully its participation in the bloc of 
pro-national forces which the MDF [Hungarian Democratic Forum] 
is trying to form? 
  [Surjan] The significance of a bloc of pro-national forces 
is 
yet to be thought through. I myself am afraid of this term. 
Naturally, we must think together, just as we have undertaken 
this -- we have even created serious tensions within the party 
-- by trying to help each other in the second round through 
withdrawing in favor of each other. Unfortunately, without 
result. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

