<H4>    KDNP Rules Out Coalition </H4>

<F P=102> LD3005180294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3005180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We have just received a report on the meeting of the 
KDNP [Christian Democratic People's Party] executive committee. 
Levente Suekoesd reports: 
  [Suekoesd] Spokeswoman Krisztina Szilagyi told our program 
that at the meeting of the KDNP executive committee today a 
decision was made to exclude the possibility of coalition with 
the MSZP [Hungarian Socialist Party]. The spokeswoman also said 
that at the meeting of the national executive to be held on 25 
June, the leadership would resign; it will operate as an acting 
body until the new leadership is elected. 

</TEXT>

