<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reach Government Headquarters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reach Government Headquarters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705145394 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1347 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2705145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 27 May -- Shortly after 1530, the head of 
Solidarity's national demonstration reached the office of the 
Council of Ministers in the center of Warsaw, as the last 
participants in the straggling march left Pilsudski Square. 
  The march was headed by a banner saying "Solidarity always 
in 
defense of your interests." The marchers chanted slogans, 
including: "Cimoszewicz must go," "SLD [Democratic Left 
Alliance] to Cuba," "An empty cell for Labor Minister Miller," 
and "Down with the commies." 
  In his speech at the rally preceding the march, Solidarity 
leader Marian Krzaklewski referred to the helicopter observing 
the preparations for the demonstration. He suggested that the 
government had already prepared a statement saying that the 
Solidarity demonstration had been a failure. 

</TEXT>

