  [Text] Manila -- The Czech-Philippine trade agreement that 
is to replace the no-longer-satisfactory treaty of 1977 was 
signed in Manila yesterday by Industry and Trade Minister Dlouhy 
and his Philippine counterpart Rizalino Navarro. Minister 
Dlouhy was also received together with other members of the 
Czech delegation by Fidel Ramos, president of the Republic of 
the Philippines, who expressed great interest of his country in 
the expansion of the relations with the Czech Republic, 
particularly in the sphere of trade. 

