<H3> <TI>   Prague Protests EC Antidumping Procedure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prague Protests EC Antidumping Procedure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2605124694 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1000 
GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2605124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The European Commission began another antidumping 
procedure against importers from the Czech Republic. This time 
the procedure concerns foundry pig iron. 
  Relevant bodies of the Czech Foreign Ministry have not yet 
received any official notification about the procedure. The 
Czech Republic's permanent mission at the European Union 
immediately protested against the Commission's one-sided 
approach, asked for information necessary to discuss specific 
trade instances, and said that the aim was to find a solution 
acceptable to both sides. 
  This is only the third instance of anti-dumping procedure 
against Czech importers since 1991. However, over the last 
two-months period this is the second instance following 
accusations levelled against Czech exporters of cement. 

</TEXT>

