<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Announcer] Franjo Tudjman, president of the 
Republic of Croatia and supreme commander of the Armed Forces, 
promoted 11 Croatian Army officers to the rank of general. 
[passage omitted] Patriotic war decorations for the 1990-92 
period were also awarded at the ceremony. Zoltan Kabok reports: 
  [Kabok] Addressing the promoted officers and high-ranking 
officials on Statehood Day, Franjo Tudjman spoke about the past 
four years, the realization of the centuries-old dream of the 
Croatian people, and the creation and strengthening of the 
Croatian Army. Three-quarters of the homeland have been 
liberated so far, and one quarter is still occupied. It is our 
historic task to liberate every inch, Tudjman stressed. 
  [Begin Tudjman recording] Of course, this is the task of the 
whole of the Croatian nation, but primarily of the Croatian 
Armed Forces, the Croatian Army. We can fulfill that task only 
if we have --as so far--a united Croatian people, and if our 
authorities keep scoring successes in economic recovery and 
international affirmation of Croatia. [end recording] 
  [Kabok] The president of the republic and supreme commander 
of the Armed Forces also spoke about Croatia's international 
position and said that we had to be ready to help the Croats in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina to ensure their survival, and that we must 
secure the strategic borders of the Croatian state. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

