<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Serbs Attack Border Area in Croatia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnian Serbs Attack Border Area in Croatia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805171694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2805171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After the Serbs based in Bosnia launched a sudden 
attack on the wider area of Zupanja in the Republic of Croatia 
with nine destructive shells at 1125 this morning, a general 
alert was sounded in Zupanja. Around midday Slavonski Samac 
also came under attack. According to a report from the Croatian 
border police, the Bosnian Serbs fired around 15 fragmentation 
shells on Slavonski Samac. There have been no casualties in 
these attacks, but huge material damage was caused. 
  In another Serb attack on the area of Orasje and Samac [in 
Bosnia] several civilians were wounded and fresh material damage 
was caused. The Serbs attacked that area with 
surface-to-surface missiles that they fired exclusively on 
civilian targets and business facilities. 

</TEXT>

