<H3> <TI>   KNSB, Employers To Hold Bilateral Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KNSB, Employers To Hold Bilateral Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005190194 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3005190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Varshava Maksimova] </F>
  [Text] Today Professor Krustyu Petkov, leader of the 
Confederation of Independent Trade Unions in Bulgaria [KNSB], 
met with the leadership of the Bulgarian Economic Chamber [BSK]. 
Both sides expressed the view that the present government has 
finally changed over to an antisocial stance. 
  After the meeting, Krustyu Petkov stated that since the 
Berov 
cabinet is illegitimate and it is impossible to conduct a 
serious dialogue with it, he will resort to an unusual approach 
for our country, namely, for the trade unions and employers to 
hold bilateral talks on topical problems. He said that tomorrow 
it is likely that the two sides -- the KNSB and BSK -- will sign 
a document in which they will call upon other social partners to 
join them. 
  This afternoon the KNSB Executive Committee held a session 
to 
discuss the draft project that the Council of Ministers has 
submitted for compensating incomes during the second quarter 
that, in his words, was like throwing dust in the eyes of the 
trade unions and the discontented population. 
  During the next few days, the KNSB will also discuss 
specific 
forms for applying trade union pressure, including boycotting 
the payment of bills for thermal and electric power, with the 
aim of unblocking the accord reached on income policy from the 
beginning of the year. 

</TEXT>

