<H3> <TI>   Committee Permits Start-Up of Kozloduy Reactor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Committee Permits Start-Up of Kozloduy Reactor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005181494 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3005181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Committee for Peaceful Uses of Atomic Energy 
has issued permission for the recommissioning of the Reactor 
Unit 1 at the Kozloduy Nuclear Power Plant, which was shut down 
16 days ago because of a leak in the air vent of its the main 
circulating pump. The unit is already connected in parallel to 
the national grid. Following a successful check on its 
condition, the No. 2 Reactor is also being prepared for start-up. 

</TEXT>

