<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croatian National Council Opposes Division </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian National Council Opposes Division </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005150194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3005150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Croatian National Council of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
at today's meeting again expressed its full support for the 
Washington Agreement, the Vienna talks, and the Constitution 
passed by the Federal Assembly. 
  The Croatian National Council does not see the federation as 
a transitional phase that threatens to divide Bosnia-Herzegovina 
in recognition of the results of the genocide, but as a 
departing point for the preservation of territorial integrity 
and the sovereignty of Bosnia-Herzegovina within internationally 
recognized borders. In this sense, the Croatian National Council 
categorically rejects any kind of negotiations about a corridor 
through the Bosnian Sava Basin because this fundamentally 
undermines the federation and the integrity of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The Croatian National Council is also opposed to the 
division 
of the territory at the ratio of 51 to 49 because in this way 
the greater parts of the Bosnian Sava Basin, Bosnian Krajina, 
the Jajce region, and others where the Croatian and the Bosniak 
majority had existed would be lost to Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The Croatian National Council of Bosnia-Herzegovina [word 
indistinct] deputies of the Croatian and Bosniak peoples, to -- 
keeping in mind their political and historic responsibility 
before their own people -- deny their voice to the solutions 
that would run contrary to the Croatian National Council's 
abovementioned stance or the results of the 1990 and 1992 
elections, which bind them to the preservation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina on the basis of equality of the three 
constituent peoples. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

