<H3> <TI>   Muslims in `All-Out Offensive' Near Tuzla </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims in `All-Out Offensive' Near Tuzla </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2705132494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1219 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2705132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bijeljina, 27 May (TANJUG) -- It has been learned 
from the press center of the eastern Bosnian corps of the army 
of the Srpska republic that Muslim forces launched an all-out 
offensive on Mt. Majevica this morning. 
  From the direction of Drijenca, Humci, Nahvioci, Brnik, 
Vrazici, and Teocak, Muslim forces launched an artillery attack 
on Serb positions and civilian targets in Priboj, Vukosavci, and 
Lopare. A tank attack was launched around 0900 and about 100 
shells were fired on these targets. A school, a church, and a 
farm in Priboj were attacked by Muslim forces and two civilians 
were wounded. 
  At around 1000, Muslim forces supported by heavy artillery 
launched an all-out infantry attack on Banj Brdo, Stolice, 
Piperi, and Spasojevici. The Serb defense forces energetically 
repelled the completely unprovoked attack and inflicted huge 
losses upon the enemy. 
  Being unable to launch an infantry breakthrough, in the 
early 
afternoon the Muslim forces started shelling Banj Brdo, Stolice, 
and civilian targets around Lopare. 
  The defense lines have not changed and there have been no 
casualties among the Serb fighters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

