<H3> <TI>   Muslims Aided by `Mercenaries' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Aided by `Mercenaries' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105150294 Pale Srpski Radio-Televizija Studio Sarajevo 
Radio in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pale Srpski Radio-Televizija Studio Sarajevo 
Radio </F>

<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The heaviest fighting in former Bosnia-Herzegovina 
in the past 24 hours was on the Donji Vakuf [Srbobran] front 
where Muslim forces are trying to break through the defense 
lines of the Srpska republic. Slavisa Zabic reports: 
  [Zabic] The strongest offensive of the Bugojno Muslims so 
far 
has been going on for three days now. Hundreds of shells of all 
calibers have hit villages around Srbobran and the city itself, 
in which civilian targets came under fire today. Very strong 
and exceptionally well armed Muslim forces, accompanied by -- as 
Serb military sources report -- many foreign mercenaries 
yesterday captured Serb villages on the Goles plateau on Mount 
Komar and razed them to the ground. Today however, the Serb 
fighters are repelling the assaults by Izetbegovic's extremists, 
the most powerful so far on the Srbobran battlefield. Both 
sides have many dead and wounded in the fighting which is 
gaining impetus hour by hour. 
  In addition to Srbobran, the final aim of the Muslim 
offensive on this part of the battlefield of the Srpska republic 
is Jajce. This is why a fresh regrouping of the enemy forces 
was observed today on roads west of Bugojno. 

</TEXT>

