<H3> <TI>   Karadzic: Abolish Sanctions First, Sign Later </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karadzic: Abolish Sanctions First, Sign Later </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2805165994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1412 GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2805165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Subotica, 28 May (TANJUG) -- Radovan Karadzic, 
president of the republic of Srpska and of the Serb Democratic 
Party [SDS], speaking in Subotica today said that the leadership 
of the Srpska republic will not sign any documents unless the 
abolition of the unfair sanctions against Serbia and Montenegro 
was given a priority treatment. 
  Karadzic was speaking at the founding assembly of the SDS 
Municipal Committee in Subotica today. Bogoljub Zelen was 
elected the committee's first chairman. The founding assembly 
was attended by Velibor Ostojic, chairman of the SDS Executive 
Committee, and numerous guests from town in Vojvodina where 
branches of this party already exist. [passage omitted] 
  Speaking about the republic of Srpska and the current 
situation, Karadzic said that during the coming talks "part of 
the territories will have to be ceded, but either the Srpska 
Assembly or the people at a referendum will decide which ones 
and how many." When the war is over the Serb people will have 
the least reasons to feel ashamed. Many crimes they did not 
commit have been attributed to them. Everyone knows who 
committed them and when and which units were involved, said 
Karadzic who spent three and a half hours in a packed hall of 
the Open University replying to numerous questions about the 
organization of a future state and the ties between the republic 
of Srpska and Serbia. 

</TEXT>

