<H3> <TI>   SPS Official: Serbia, FRY Enduring Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPS Official: Serbia, FRY Enduring Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005095694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3005095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Goran Percevic, vice president of the Socialist 
Party of Serbia [SPS], in a statement for Belgrade Radio 
maintains that the sanctions against the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia [FRY] that were imposed two years ago had the goal of 
destroying Serbia economically and thwarting its policy of aid 
and solidarity with the struggle of the Serbian people in the 
republic of Srpska and the republic of Serbian Krajina. Two 
years later, we can say that Serbia and the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia have managed to withstand this terrible pressure -- 
that is, that the sanctions have not accomplished their goal -- 
said Percevic, and added that Serbia had had a dignified 
response to this attempt at economic destruction. I believe 
that this latest economic program that is being implemented in 
Serbia represents an economic response to the attempt at 
economic genocide over our country and people, said SPS Vice 
President Goran Percevic, in a statement for Radio Belgrade on 
the second anniversary of the sanctions. 

</TEXT>

