<H3> <TI>   Serbs Launch Day-Long Attacks on Gradacac </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Launch Day-Long Attacks on Gradacac </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3105194094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3105194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified correspondent from the Information </F>
Center of the 107th Chivalrous Motorized Brigade of Gradacac] 
  [Excerpt] Attacks on the free territory of Gradacac have 
lasted all day, since early this morning. The projectiles from 
all types of weapons are showering the positions of our fighters 
and the central part of the free territory. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Three tanks and numerous 
mortars, guns, howitzers from all the well-known chetnik 
strongholds took part in the attack today. After two infantry 
attacks had been successfully repelled, with the enemy suffering 
major losses, artillery continued to attack the town and the 
entire front. These attacks are mainly indiscriminate, nervous, 
and without a particular aim. Stunned by yet another defeat, 
the Serbo-fascists have been pounding the town all afternoon. 
[passage omitted] 

