<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-105 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  1 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Intensify Brcko Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Intensify Brcko Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0106090994 </F>
<F P=103> AU0106090994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Network in Serbo-Croatian at 0800 GMT on 1 June carries in its 
regular 7-minute newscast two reports on the combat situation on 
the Brcko and Gracanica fronts. 
  Brcko correspondent Hamid Deronjic reports that "the Serbian 
aggressor's provocations that characterized the day [31 May] on 
the Brcko front intensified during the night. In the evening 
hours, the chetniks used 62 and 80-mm mortars, Tromblon 
grenades, and infantry weapons to pound the Brcko defense 
positions. On several occasions, the chetniks from (?Lipe) 
opened fierce fire at the central part of the defense. At 2115, 
the enemy used a hill gun to shell the wider area of Bajici but 
to no avail. The first morning hours on the Brcko front are 
marked by the Serbian aggressor's small arms' provocations, 
which are particularly pronounced in the region of Djukici. The 
defenders are not responding." 
  Izudin Durakovic, the correspondent from Gracanica, 
recapitulates the situation on the front in the past 24 hours 
and adds that "the shelling from howitzers, tanks, and Bofors 
from [name indistinct] and Besanj continued in the evening 
hours. Enemy vehicles were on the move throughout the day, 
bringing in fresh forces and hardware. In the 117th Lukavac 
Brigade theater of operations, the chetniks used a Broving and 
anti-aircraft guns to shell Malinjak. The night was more quiet 
than usual for this part of the front." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-30844 </DOCNO>
