<F P=100> SLOVENIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drnovsek Discusses Conflict With Italy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Drnovsek Discusses Conflict With Italy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3105084294 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
2000 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3105084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Slovene </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek in an interview for 
REUTERS explained the government views about a recent 
Slovene-Italian conflict. He gave his assurance that our 
country intends to persist in its views regarding its heritage 
from World War II and expressed belief that the European Union 
will support us in this. He warned that, if Italy continues to 
exert pressure upon our country in the future, Slovenia will 
demand compensation for the time of occupation by Fascist Italy 
and protection for approximately 100,000 Slovenes in Italy. He 
did not ascribe any major significance to a recent Italian move, 
when at the Conference on Stability in Europe Slovenia was cut 
from the list of countries that are potential EU members at the 
insistence of the Rome authorities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

