<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy Holds Tactical Exercise in Adriatic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy Holds Tactical Exercise in Adriatic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105165394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1639 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3105165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Tivat, Yugoslavia, May 31 (TANJUG) -- The Yugoslav 
naval command has prepared and performed a several-day tactical 
exercise with the use of live ammunition, the information 
service of the Yugoslav Army General Staff said on Tuesday [31 
May]. The exercise was carried out within the realisation of 
the tasks of this year's combat training aimed at checking the 
combat and operational-tactical readiness and degree of training 
of the Yugoslav naval command and its units in the defence of 
the Yugoslav part of the Adriatic coast. Tested were the 
organisation and performance of the anti-combat defence of the 
Yugoslav part of the coast in case of an aggression on 
Yugoslavia (Serbia/Montenegro), with the support of the military 
air force and anti-aircraft defence, it was said. 
  Acccording to its contents and dynamism, the exercise 
represents one of the most complex forms of testing the degree 
of combat readiness of navy units for fighting targets at sea, 
land or in the air. At the end of the exercise, the navy 
performed shooting exercises with torpedoes, artillery and 
anti-submarine ammunition. The final part of the exercise was 
watched by the Yugoslav president and the president of the 
Supreme Defence Council, Zoran Lilic, Montenegrin President and 
member of the Supreme Defence Council, Momir Bulatovic, the 
Yugoslav Army chief of general staff, Colonel General Momcilo 
Perisic and the commanders of the Yugoslav army strategic 
groups. Lilic, Bulatovic and Gen. Perisic agreed that the 
degree of training of the fleet and coastal defence was high, as 
well as their readiness to successfully deal with all kinds of 
threats to Yugoslavia's territorial integrity and sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

