<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   SZDSZ Chairman Views Coalition Possibilities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SZDSZ Chairman Views Coalition Possibilities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3105163594 Budapest PESTI HIRLAP in Hungarian 31 May 94 pp 
1, 3 </F>

<F P=103> AU3105163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest PESTI HIRLAP </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["B.A.P."-signed interview with Ivan Peto, chairman of the </F>
Alliance of Free Democrats; place and date not given: "Eternal 
Second?"] 
  [Text] The Alliance of Free Democrats [SZDSZ] cannot 
initiate coalition steps, and no signal has yet arrived from the 
Hungarian Socialist Party [MSZP], SZDSZ Chairman Ivan Peto told 
us when we asked him about his party's election results and 
coalition possibilities. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] The SZDSZ finished in second place in both 
free elections so far. In the last issue of MAGYAR NARANCS 
[HUNGARIAN ORANGE], socialist political scientist Mihaly Bihari 
drew the conclusion that no liberal party can win in Hungary. 
Is there any truth in this? 
  [Peto] I could refute this if the SZDSZ won the elections, 
but I think this was not the first mistake of Mihaly Bihari. It 
is not fortunate to come up with such an eternal judgment that a 
party always finishes second, because it generally does not 
happen so. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] Some people assume that the SZDSZ is 
hesitating to form a coalition because this way an 
MSZP-Hungarian Democratic Forum [MDF] government alliance could 
emerge and these two parties will soon lose value and then the 
SZDSZ will remain the only marketable political force. 
  [Peto] I have not yet heard about this assumption. On such 
a basis, one could also consider the possibility of an MSZP- 
Independent Smallholders' Party [FKGP] coalition. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] on the eve of the elections, [trade union 
chief] Sandor Nagy said that his party thinks in terms of a 
coalition anyway. If the SZDSZ is not willing to form such a 
coalition, they will form an alliance with another party. 
  [Peto] Apart from the SZDSZ and the MSZP, there are still 
four other parliamentary parties. They can also think of the 
Federation of Young Democrats [Fidesz], the Christian Democratic 
People's Party [KDNP], and the FKGP. I do not want to deal with 
every possibility separately. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] In view of the election results, the first 
half of the runners ends with the MDF. The other three parties 
are lagging far behind the front runners. 
  [Peto] The MSZP does not need to form an alliance with a big 
party; they can form a coalition with any small party if any of 
these parties is willing. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] The head of the MSZP list already declared 
that they are thinking in terms of a coalition anyway. However, 
there is not yet a relevant answer from the head of the SZDSZ 
list. 
  [Peto] I said to this that if a party does not have a 
parliamentary majority, we consider it to be necessary; if it 
has a parliamentary majority, we consider it to be possible. I 
have nothing to say in addition to this. There is not yet any 
coalition offer whatsoever at the moment; only the intention for 
a coalition has been declared so far. No one called upon us 
with a coalition offer. We cannot initiate anything with our 
17-18 percent. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] Peter Hack said in one of the dailies that he 
would not take the SZDSZ into a coalition in this political 
situation. 
  [Peto] He was correct in declaring this. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] Does that mean that Ivan Peto also thinks so? 
  [Peto] As the SZDSZ chairman, I think that I should not 
treat the public with my own private opinions. Of course, I 
have my own private opinion, but the party should form its 
opinion. I said that in the case of an absolute majority, the 
chances of a coalition are much smaller -- at least on our part 
-- than in case there were not such an absolute majority. 
  [PESTI HIRLAP] However, you did not exclude the possibility 
of a government coalition with the MSZP. 
  [Peto] Nor did Peter Hack. He said that, on his part, he 
would not support such a proposal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-30876 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu105_h_94002" </HT>


