<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Army Corps Established in Iasi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Army Corps Established in Iasi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20777A Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA in Romanian 8 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20777A </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unsigned article: "A New Army Corps Has Been Established on </F>
the Eastern Border"] 
  [Text] Major General Viorel Cheptine, commander of the Iasi 
garrison, has announced the establishment of a new army corps in 
the municipality. The general reported his decision on the 
occasion of the swearing-in ceremony for the members of the 
"Stefan cel Mare" [Stephen the Great] mechanized division. The 
new army corps has been established in accordance with the new 
military strategy of Romania and is intended to reinforce 
Romanian military dispositions in the eastern part of the 
country, in a particularly sensitive zone. In accordance with 
the organizational structure of the Romanian Army, an army corps 
is composed of three divisions. 

</TEXT>

