<H4>    Spokesman Cites Havel on Visit </H4>

<F P=102> AU3005175394 Prague CTK in English 1611 GMT 30 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3005175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague May 30 (CTK) -- In connection with the 
announced visit of Chilean Ground Forces Chief Commander Augusto 
Pinochet, President Vaclav Havel believes that it would benefit 
Czech-Chilean relations if they were developed by figures 
respected in the democratic world, Havel's spokesman Ladislav 
Spacek told CTK today. 
  "The president is convinced that the democratic system in 
Chile is lasting and stable. But it would benefit bilateral 
relations between the Czech Republic and Chile if they were 
developed by personalities who are accepted in the democratic 
world without reservations," Spacek said. He said the 
Presidential Office had today received letters from journalists 
addressed to Havel and denouncing Pinochet's visit. Spacek said 
that Havel already spoke critically of the forthcoming visit at 
a press conference in Bratislava last Thursday [26 May]. 
  "The visit does not have an official character and neither 
the president nor his office has been informed of it in advance. 
The Czech Republic is opening its border to all people having 
valid travel documents. The president only takes note of the 
visit," Spacek said. 

</TEXT>

