  [Text] Prague May 30 (CTK) -- Former Chilean President 
Augusto Pinochet should not have been granted an entry visa to 
the Czech Republic, Interior Minister Jan Ruml told Czech 
Television today. A Chilean military delegation arrived today 
in Prague to negotiate arms deals with the Omnipol company, but 
the arrival of Chilean Ground Forces Chief Commander Augusto 
Pinochet has not been confirmed although it had been notified. 
  "However, if he got it and is here, I will not draw any 
conclusion as interior minister," Ruml added. The Interior 
Ministry will not provide protection to Pinochet because his 
visit is private and the Foreign Ministry has not asked for it, 
Ruml said. 

