<H3> <TI>   Chile's Pinochet Arrives on Unofficial Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chile's Pinochet Arrives on Unofficial Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Anti-Pinochet Protest at Embassy </H4>

<F P=102> AU3005190094 Prague CTK in English 1827 GMT 30 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3005190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague May 30 (CTK) -- "Murderer, where are our 
brothers?" reads the banner unfolded today by Jan Chladek and 
Marek Mamon outside the Chilean Embassy. A Chilean military 
delegation arrived today in Prague, but the arrival of Chilean 
Ground Forces Chief Commander Augusto Pinochet has not been 
confirmed although it had been notified. 
  Chladek said that Pinochet's visit had a special meaning for 
him. He said he was born in Chile to a Czech father and Chilean 
mother whose family had suffered a great deal under Pinochet's 
regime, losing several of its members. After a calm 
intervention by the Czech Police, the demonstrators removed the 
banner. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

