<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chile's Pinochet Arrives on Unofficial Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Baudys Denies `Official Contacts' </H4>

<F P=102> AU3105132294 Prague CTK in English 1032 GMT 31 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3105132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague May 31 (CTK) -- The Czech Army does not as 
yet have any official contacts with Chile as regards possible 
cooperation, Defence Minister Antonin Baudys told CTK today. He 
said that with its security in mind, the Czech Republic had to 
cooperate not only with its neighbours, but with countries where 
possible cooperation was of both a military and industrial 
nature, such as Israel, China and other countries. 
  The Czech Defence Ministry had as yet not even considered 
the 
thought of possible cooperation with Chile, he said, adding that 
it was not planning to meet with former dictator Augusto 
Pinochet, now head of the Chilean ground forces, who arrived in 
Prague yesterday. Baudys stressed that the visit was private. 
Baudys was unable to say if the Czech Republic had exported any 
arms to Chile since 1989. 

</TEXT>

