<H3> <TI>   Unofficial Final Election Results Published </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unofficial Final Election Results Published </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3105071494 Budapest MTI in English 2016 GMT 30 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3105071494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 30 May (MTI) -- In the May 29 second round 
of the 1994 parliamentary elections, 55.12 percent of eligible 
voters, numbering 4,339,801, turned out for the vote, and 
4,286,373 (98.77 percent) cast valid ballots, Chairman of the 
National Electoral Committee Janos Nemeth told an international 
news conference in the Parliament building today. 
  According to an unofficial, computerized summary, the 
Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP) won 209 mandates in the 
386-member Parliament, the Alliance of Free Democrats (SZDSZ) 
70, the Hungarian Democratic Forum (HDF) 37, the Independent 
Smallholders Party (FKGP) 26, the Christian Democratic People's 
Party (KDNP) 22, the Federation of Young Democrats (Fidesz) 20, 
and the Agrarian Association and the four-party liberal 
coalition one each. 
  Accordingly, the MSZP won 54.15 percent of seats, the SZDSZ 
18.14 percent, the HDF 9.59 percent, the FKGP 6.74 percent, the 
KDNP 5.7 percent, the Fidesz 5.18 percent, and the Agrarian 
Association and the four-party liberal coalition 0.26 percent 
each. 
  The MSZP triumphed in 149 individual constituencies, the 
SZDSZ in 17, the HDF in four, the KDNP in three, and the FKGP, 
the Agrarian Association, and the four-party liberal coalition 
in one each. 
  The MSZP won 53 mandates on regional lists, the SZDSZ 28, 
the 
HDF 18, the FKGP 14, the Fidesz seven and, the KDNP five. 
  Seats from the national lists were distributed as follows: 
SZDSZ 25, HDF 15, KDNP 14, Fidesz 13, FKGP 11, MSZP seven. 

</TEXT>

