<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech President Visits, Meets Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech President Visits, Meets Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605203494 Prague CTK in English 1711 GMT 26 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2605203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, May 26 (CTK) -- At today's meeting with 
Slovak President Michal Kovac, Czech President Vaclav Havel 
pointed out the restrained Czech attitude to Slovak politics, 
Havel told journalists. 
  "It would be unwise if the Czech card is played during the 
coming election campaign," he said, referring to allegations of 
Slovak federalism. 
  In the Czech Republic or Slovakia there are no serious 
forces 
wishing for the restoration of Czechoslovakia, Kovac said. 
  The validity of Benes decrees has not been questioned in 
Slovakia, he said. 
  Havel said he was glad Slovakia had joined the border 
regime. 
Border procedures are time-consuming and facilities are on a 
lower level than on the borders with other neighboring 
countries, Kovac said, adding that more finance and better 
administration are needed. "The (Czech and Slovak) Governments 
are aware of the painful situation and will have to resolve it 
promptly," Kovac said. Kovac and Havel are to meet next in 
Prague after the Slovak elections. 

</TEXT>

