<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: HZDS Would Win 21 Percent of Vote </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll: HZDS Would Win 21 Percent of Vote </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005185494 Prague CTK in English 1744 GMT 30 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3005185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava May 30 (CTK) -- Most Slovaks (around 21 
percent) would vote for former Premier Vladimir Meciar's HZDS 
(Movement for a Democratic Slovakia), a poll conducted by the 
independent Focus agency in May revealed. 
  Then HZDS is followed by the Democratic Left Party (SDL) 
with 
12 percent, the Christian Democratic Movement (KDH) with 7 
percent, Slovak Workers' Party (SSD, 7 percent) and Premier 
Jozef Moravcik's Democratic Union of Slovakia (DEUS, 6 percent). 
  The rest of the parties would not cross the five-percent 
barrier necessary for entering the parliament. 
  These results somewhat differ from those obtained by the 
Slovak Statistical Office, according to which the HZDS would 
receive 27 percent, the SDL 16 percent, the KDH 11 percent, the 
SSD three percent and the DEUS five percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

