<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs To Give Construction Sites to Settlers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs To Give Construction Sites to Settlers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705161494 Tirana ATA in English 1024 GMT 27 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2705161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, May 27 (ATA) -- In the context of the 
programs for colonization of Kosova, Serbian authorities warned 
that they will give 200 construction sites to the Serbian 
settlers in the Istog commune. The settlers are mainly refugees 
who have fled from Bosnia or Croatia. The sites will be 
delivered in Istog, Dubrave, Muzhevine, Gjurakoc, Banje, and 
other areas. 
  On the other side, the Albanians in the Istog commune has 
been given no construction sites. 

</TEXT>

